@endnode

@node "BBShareWare" "ShareWare"
@prev "Main"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}ShareWare@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 Shareware  programs  are  freely  distributable  (in  their demo and limited
 version  as  stated in the title bar and into the information window).  Once
 you have tried the program for a limited period of time (about a month), you
 can  decide whether to send the registration fee requested by the @{"author" link "BBAuthor" 0}.
 Those  who  choose  to  do  so  will  receive a fully-functional  registered
 version  and  a  special personalized key (which can't be given to anybody);
 they  will  also  be  entitled  to  purchase possible future updates at very
 special  prices.   The final user is morally (and legally) bound not to copy
 to others either his/her key or the registered version.

 Since  the  provided  personal keyfile also contains registered user's data,
 it's  advisable  not  to give it to others.  For the same reason the keyfile
 cannot be sold.
@endnode

@node "BBInstall" "Installation"
@prev "Main"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Installation@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 To install BancaBase just double click on the INSTALL icon. The installation
 will  be  performed  by  the  standard Installer program; every step will be
 commented by the procedure at the moment of its execution.

 A complete installation requires about 1 MB of free hard disk space.

 Please read carefully the sections of this manual about @{"Hardware" link "BBResources" 0} and
@{"Software"  link  "BBResources" 0} resources required by the program.

@endnode

@node "BBResources" "HardWare & SoftWare requirements"
@prev "Main"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}HardWare e SoftWare requirements@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 @{b}Minimum Hardware Equipment required:@{ub}
 -----------------------------------

-  Any Amiga model

-  AGA or ECS graphics (500kb of free graphics mem)

-  CPU 68000 or higher

-  Some Fastmem (recommended but not mandatory)

-  Hard Disk


 @{b}Software requirements:@{ub}
 ---------------------

-  Operating system 2.0 or higher, correctly installed.

   The program also utilizes some specific 3.0 and 3.1 features, but only
   if available on system.


 CyberGFX (8 bit) modes are supported as well.
@endnode

@node "Menus" "The 4 Sections"
@prev "Main"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}BancaBase Menus@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 The  program is divided into four main sections and each section collects all
 the functions related to a specific topic. For example, the "Archive" section
 includes  specific  functions  to  create/delete/mantain  BancaBase  archives.
 The same applies to the others.

 Here they are :

 @{"-- Archive Management Menu --" link "ArchiveMenu" 0}

 @{"-- Main Menu --" link "MainMenu" 0}

 @{"-- Budget Management Menu --" link "BalanceMenu" 0}

 @{"-- Reports and Statistics Menu --" link "ReportsMenu" 0}

 Obviously,  directly selecting a function via pull-down menus is simpler and
 allows  immediate  access  to the desired function, without having to browse
 through the program sections mentioned just above.
@endnode


@node "ArchiveMenu" "Archive Menu"
@prev "Menus"
@next "MainMenu"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}The Archive Management Menu@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 This  menu  includes all the functions needed to maintain its archives, like
 create, delete, etc.

 These  functions  always require you to select an archive, since the program
 can be in this menu only when no archive is yet loaded into memory.

 This is also the menu the program shows when started and whenever you select
 the @{"Close Archive" link "CloseArc" 0} function.

@endnode

@node "MainMenu" "Main Menu"
@prev "ArchiveMenu"
@next "BalanceMenu"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Main Menu@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 This  menu  contains  some  first  function  to  operate  on the just loaded
 archive.  You  can  modify  its  configuration  and parameters, like records
 color, currency preferences, maximums, etc.

 All  modifications performed via this menu refer to the loaded archive only,
 whose  name  (or rather description) is constantly showed in the bottom left
 frame.

 To perform operations on records you have to enter the @{"Budget Management Menu" link "BalanceMenu" 0}.
@endnode

@node "BalanceMenu" "Budget Management Menu"
@prev "MainMenu"
@next "ReportsMenu"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Budget Management Menu@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 This  program  section  contains functions which allow to insert, modify and
 delete records of the loaded archive.

To  show  statement  of  account,  incomes-expenses and statistic charts just
enter @{"Reports and Statistics Menu" link "ReportsMenu" 0}.
@endnode


@node "ReportsMenu" "Statement of Account / Charts Menu"
@prev "BalanceMenu"
@next "Menus"

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Charts and Statistics Menu@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

 This  section is dedicated to  functions which  allow generation of reports,
 statement of account and statistics.

 There  is  also  an option to set the preferences for all generated reports,
 like number of lines per page, whether to include FormFeeds at the bottom of
 pages, etc

 This is the last section of the program.
@endnode

